scenario_a.name: Cheap Renewables Only
scenario_a.description: Low renewable costs, high clean firm costs — no investment signal for FOAK
scenario_a.method_description: Sequential optimization: resources deployed at each threshold become the floor for the next. Cheapest $/tCO2 at each step, but locked into prior commitments.

scenario_b.name: Clean Firm Investment
scenario_b.description: Low costs across all clean technologies — FOAK learning curve success
scenario_b.method_description: All buyers target 95% CFE simultaneously. Optimal mix at 95% with Low clean firm costs is the portfolio. FOAK investment drives learning curves to NOAK pricing.
